Derived code and attribution
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

mfx is part of the *mpump* family of local-first browser instruments by the
same author. All sibling projects are licensed AGPL-3.0-or-later, and the code
reused here is reused under AGPL-3.0-or-later with attribution within the same
author and suite. The following portions are derived from sibling projects:

* The Ableton Link bridge client (src/transport/linkBridge.ts) — derived from
  **mspectr**.

* The mbus tab-to-tab audio client (src/transport/mbus/) — vendored **verbatim**
  from **mbus** (packages/mbus-client: client.ts, protocol.ts; the index.ts
  re-export carries this credit). The suite has no shared package registry yet,
  so the library is copied and credited rather than imported; it is kept
  byte-for-byte with upstream so it stays trivially re-syncable — change it
  upstream and re-copy, never edit here.

These derivations were confirmed by the suite lead. Because every source project
is AGPL-3.0-or-later by the same author, the reuse is covered by that license;
this NOTICE records the lineage for attribution and transparency.
